# Researcher seed accounts (TEMPLATE)

Curated list of high-signal creators to scan for content ideas. Edit to match YOUR network and taste.

## X (Twitter)

API user IDs cached so we skip per-run lookups. Run the resolution curl below to get IDs.

| Handle | User ID | Why track |
|---|---|---|
| `@romanbuildsaas` | `1893653481858433024` | (example · metrics-first build-in-public · raw revenue + DAU posts) |
| `@MichLieben` | `512156315` | (example · story + self-roast register) |
| `@itsalexvacca` | `859850213015597056` | (example · operator-with-receipts) |
| `<your handle>` | `<your ID>` | <add your own seed accounts here> |

Add new handles by running once with the X API user-by-username lookup
to get the numeric ID, then commit it back here.

```bash
source ./.env
curl -s "https://api.twitter.com/2/users/by/username/<handle>" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ${X_BEARER_TOKEN}"
```

(Auth uses `<YOUR_X_BEARER_TOKEN>` set as `X_BEARER_TOKEN` in `./.env`.)

## LinkedIn

Profile IDs are Unipile-style `ACoAA...` strings. Resolve via Unipile profile-search on first lookup, cache here.

| Name | LinkedIn URL | Profile ID (cache) | Why track |
|---|---|---|---|
| <example name> | linkedin.com/in/example | TBD | (example · adjust to your taste) |
| <example name> | linkedin.com/in/example-2 | TBD | (example · adjust to your taste) |
| <example name> | linkedin.com/in/example-3 | TBD | (example · adjust to your taste) |
| You (your own profile) | linkedin.com/in/your-handle | `<YOUR_LINKEDIN_PROFILE_ID>` | Your own feed (for "what people respond to me about") |

Resolve a profile ID:

```bash
source ./.env
curl -s "https://${UNIPILE_DSN}/api/v1/users?account_id=${UNIPILE_ACCOUNT_ID}&keyword=<name>&limit=5" \
  -H "X-API-KEY: ${UNIPILE_API_KEY}"
```

(Auth uses `<YOUR_UNIPILE_DSN>`, `<YOUR_UNIPILE_API_KEY>`, `<YOUR_UNIPILE_ACCOUNT_ID>` set in `./.env`.)

## Notion data sources

| Source | Data source ID | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Content DB | `<YOUR_NOTION_CONTENT_DB_ID>` | Your published rows (performance scan) |
| Human Notes / Interview DB | `<YOUR_NOTION_HUMAN_NOTES_DB_ID>` | Customer-interview transcripts (customer scan) |

Customer-scan filter: include rows matching your interview categories. Edit the filter list in researcher/SKILL.md to match your DB schema.

## Topic seeds (for keyword scans)

